headline: DHI Q3 Deep Dive: Incentives and Market Caution Shape Outlook Amid Margin Compression
summary: Homebuilder D.R. Horton (NYSE:DHI) announced better-than-expected revenue in Q3 CY2025, but sales fell by 3.2% year on year to $9.68 billion. On the other hand, the company’s full-year revenue guidance of $34.25 billion at the midpoint came in 1.7% below analysts’ estimates. Its GAAP profit of $3.04 per share was 7.6% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
